message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The symptoms and ultrasound findings suggest an androgen-secreting ovarian tumor, and the microscopic examination confirms the presence of Theca interna cells. These cells are involved in steroidogenesis and are responsible for androgen secretion in females. Granulosa cells produce estrogen, Sertoli cells are present in males and Clue cells are associated with bacterial vaginosis.

Granulosa cells are responsible for estrogen production, Sertoli cells are found in the testes and Clue cells are associated with bacterial vaginosis.
